title: Over the Door Storage
description: Watch this video on how to maximize your storage space in a dorm room.

transcripts:
Dorm rooms and small apartments never have enough space to store your clothing and accessories like purses, scarves, shoes, and hats. Try a surprising store solution-- your door. The back of the door is perfect for storing shoes and there is lots of options. Get an over the door shoe rack and a color to match your decor or show off your shoe collection with one that aligns them up. Up to 36 pairs. 

If you're more about the purses than the shoes, no problem, they've got a rack for that.  There's one that's great for holding scarves too. And your hats, you're all set with this hanger made for them. If your closet just cutting it, try a back of the door closet rod. It adds a ton of extra hanging space. You'll find lot's of uses for a row of hooks that doesn't require hammering holes in the door and walls. There is an over the door hamper too. Mix and match to create a storage solution that looks great too. 

Now don't you forget about the front of the door. Use it for sharing notes, pictures, or artwork that says something about you. The door is a fun place to add a personal decorative touch. Maybe you can give visitors a hint of who's behind the door. Create a place on your door to capture messages. To and from your friends sometimes. Sometimes texting doesn't have the same charm. For great storage options and personalized decor look no further than your own front door.
